se.cbb.jprime.prm

Class Structure

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.cbb.jprime.prm.Structure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Structure>

    public class Structure
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Structure>
    Holds a PRM structure, that is, a set of parent-child dependencies. Two instances of this class are considered equal if they contain equivalent dependencies.
    Author:

      • getInverseDependencies

        public java.util.Collection<Dependencies> getInverseDependencies(ProbAttribute parent)
        Returns all dependencies in which a specific attribute is a parent. If none, an empty collection is returned. See also getDependencies(...).
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent attribute.
        Returns:
        the parent-child dependencies for the parent.

      • getDependencies

        public java.util.Collection<Dependencies> getDependencies()
        Returns all dependencies, collected by common child. There will be a collection also for attributes which are not children in any dependencies.
        Returns:
        for every probabilistic attribute, the dependencies in which the attribute is a child (possibly 0).

      • getSources

        public java.util.Set<ProbAttribute> getSources()
